5.Model Evaluation:
•
Evaluate model performance using standard metrics, including accuracy, precision, recall, and F1-score, to assess how effectively the machine learning model classifies underground mine conditions as safe, warning, or dangerous based on IoT sensor data.
•
Use confusion matrices to analyze classification errors, identify false alarms or missed gas-risk conditions, and improve the reliability of real-time gas monitoring and alert generation.
•
Compare the performance of multiple machine learning models to select the best-performing algorithm for deployment in the IoT-based underground gas monitoring system.
• 6.Real-Time Prediction System:
• IoT-based underground gas sensors continuously stream real-time data (methane, carbon monoxide, oxygen) to a central system using UHF wireless communication.
•
AI/ML models process the incoming data in real time, performing preprocessing, feature extraction, and inference to classify mine conditions as safe, warning, or dangerous.
•
Automated alerts and control actions are triggered based on model predictions, including alarms, ventilation adjustments, and power cut interlocks to prevent gas-related accidents
7.Monitoring Dashboard & Alerts:
•
Design an IoT-based real-time monitoring dashboard that displays underground gas parameters such as methane (CH₄), carbon monoxide (CO), carbon dioxide (CO₂), and oxygen (O₂), along with live trends and sensor status from different Mine locations.
•
Visualize AI/ML-based risk classification on the dashboard by categorizing mine conditions into safe, warning, and high-risk levels, and showing gas concentration trends over time for early decision-making.
•
Generate automated alerts and notifications when predicted gas levels exceed safety limits, including visual warnings on the dashboard and real-time notifications (SMS/email/control room alerts) to responsible mine personnel for fast actions.
Output — Frontend Design:
After completing the real-time data processing and AI/ML model inference, the system provides an intuitive IoT-based frontend dashboard for underground mine gas monitoring and safety management. The output includes:
