1. Live Gas Parameter Visualization:
The dashboard displays real-time values and trend graphs of underground gas parameters such as methane (CH₄), carbon monoxide (CO), carbon dioxide (CO₂), and oxygen (O₂). These visualizations help operators understand current gas conditions and observe short-term and long-term changes predicted by the AI model.
2. Mine Safety Status Classification:
Based on machine learning predictions, the system classifies each mine zone into safety levels:
•
Safe → Normal operating conditions with continuous monitoring.
•
Warning → Caution advisory indicating rising gas levels.
•
High Risk → Critical condition with immediate alerts and safety actions.
This classification is clearly shown using color-coded indicators for quick decision-making.
