3. Automated Alerts and Notifications:
When the AI/ML model detects abnormal or high-risk gas conditions, the system automatically generates alerts, including visual warnings on the dashboard, sound alarms in the control room, and SMS/email notifications to responsible mine personnel for immediate response.
4. Zone-Based Monitoring and Location Mapping:
The frontend displays mine zone status (goaf edges, return airways, electrical zones, longwall face) with real-time sensor health and risk levels. Interactive layouts help identify the exact location of gas accumulation and support faster safety interventions.
5. Historical Logs and Reports:
The system maintains time-stamped records of gas measurements, AI model predictions, alerts, and system actions. These logs support trend analysis, safety audits, and regulatory compliance.
